{"id": 15415, "date": "1988-03-20T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1988-03-20T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=15415"}, "modified": "2026-02-08T07:37:21", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-08T15:37:21", "slug": "matr-bob-seger-and-bruce-springsteen-old-time-rock-and-roll", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/03/20/matr-bob-seger-and-bruce-springsteen-old-time-rock-and-roll/", "title": {"rendered": "Old Time Rock and Roll"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>There&#8217;s no official video for the studio version of Bob Seger&#8217;s &#8220;Old Time Rock and Roll.&#8221;</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s just as well, because come on: how could any video compete with the iconic movie scene it&#8217;s most associated with?</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8elAi-7G0OE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;Old Time Rock and Roll&#8221; charted in the Top 100 twice&#8211;once when it was originally released in the spring of 1979 (it peaked at #28), and again in 1983 when <em>Risky Business\u00a0</em>was released (peaking at #48).</p>\n<p>But despite their long-time association (they first played together in 1980), Bob and Bruce didn&#8217;t perform the song together until Seger&#8217;s Madison Square Garden concert on December 1, 2011.</p>\n<p>It was worth the wait. Turn the volume up, switch to full-screen mode, and enjoy:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/gFKmo9f5EIs?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bob and Bruce&#8217;s team-up was pretty spectacular, considering they&#8217;d never played the song together before.</p>\n<p>But while Bruce might have never played &#8220;Old Time Rock and Roll&#8221; with the song&#8217;s original recording artist before, he&#8217;d actually played it live one time prior&#8230; all the way back in 1989 in one of his legendary surprise appearances at The Stone Pony with house band Cats on a Smooth Surface.</p>\n<p>That performance is a lot harder to find than the 2011, but here it is for your listening pleasure. From Sunday night, July 23, 1989, check out Bruce Springsteen with Cats on a Smooth Surface playing Bruce&#8217;s very first performance of &#8220;Old Time Rock and Roll.&#8221; It&#8217;s incomplete, but it&#8217;s still a fun listen.</p>\n<div id=\"v-bLlxnLzl-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/bLlxnLzl?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><strong>Old Time Rock and Roll<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> July 23, 1989 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> December 1, 2011 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 February 1, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce has played Bob Seger&#8217;s &#8220;Old Time Rock and Roll&#8221; in concert twice: once in 2011 with Seger himself, and once way back in a 1980s club appearance. Catch both fun performances inside.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 15806, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4, 3609, 5], "tags": [687, 640, 1940], "class_list": ["post-15415", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-little-help", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-bob-seger", "tag-cats-on-a-smooth-surface", "tag-old-time-rock-and-roll"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/bob-seger-and-the-silver-bullet-band-sunspot-baby-capitol.jpg?fit=800%2C792&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-40D", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 17366, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/04/14/cover-me-ramblin-gamblin-man/", "url_m